PREFIX s223: <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#>
PREFIX ex: <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223/data/lbnl-example-2#>

SELECT DISTINCT ?zone WHERE {
  ?zone a s223:Zone .
  {
    # Directly associated property
    ?zone s223:hasProperty ?prop .
    ?prop a ?propClass .
    FILTER(?propClass IN (
      s223:QuantifiableObservableProperty,
      s223:EnumeratedObservableProperty,
      s223:QuantifiableActuatableProperty,
      s223:EnumeratedActuatableProperty
    ))
  }
  UNION
  {
    # Indirect connection via a RoomDomainSpace and any chain of connection predicates
    ?zone s223:hasDomainSpace* ?ds .
    ?ds a ex:RoomDomainSpace .
    ?ds (s223:connected|s223:connectedTo|s223:connectedFrom|s223:connectsThrough|s223:connectedThrough)* ?prop .
    ?prop a ?propClass .
    FILTER(?propClass IN (
      s223:QuantifiableObservableProperty,
      s223:EnumeratedObservableProperty,
      s223:QuantifiableActuatableProperty,
      s223:EnumeratedActuatableProperty
    ))
  }
}

ModelResponse(parts=[TextPart(content='{\n  "sparql_query": "PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>\\nPREFIX brick: <https://brickschema.org/schema/Brick/>\\nPREFIX std223: <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#>\\n\\nSELECT DISTINCT ?zoneLabel ?propLabel ?alcEndpoint ?mpcEndpoint WHERE {\\n  # --- Zones -------------------------------------------------------\\n  ?zone a std223:Zone .\\n  OPTIONAL { ?zone rdfs:label ?zoneLabel }\\n\\n  # --- Two ways a Property can be associated with the Zone ----------\\n  {\\n    # Direct association\\n    ?zone std223:hasProperty ?prop .\\n  } UNION {\\n    # Indirect association via a RoomDomainSpace reached in two \\"hasDomainSpace\\" steps\\n    # (Zone --hasDomainSpace--> ?intermediate --hasDomainSpace--> ?roomDomainSpace)\\n    ?zone std223:hasDomainSpace ?intermediate .\\n    ?intermediate std223:hasDomainSpace ?roomDomainSpace .\\n    # The RoomDomainSpace (or any intermediate space) \\"contains\\" the Property\\n    ?roomDomainSpace std223:contains ?prop .\\n  }\\n\\n  # --- Property details --------------------------------------------\\n  ?prop rdfs:label ?propLabel .\\n  ?prop std223:hasExternalReference ?extRef .\\n\\n  # Only keep ExternalReferences that are NOT writable\\n  ?extRef brick:writable false .\\n\\n  # --- Endpoints ---------------------------------------------------\\n  # The same ExternalReference can hold two endpoint values  one for the\\n  # ALC system and one for the MPC system.  They are both attached with the\\n  # generic Brick:endpoint predicate; the value itself encodes the type.\\n  # We separate them by looking at the literal string (\\"alc\\" vs \\"mpc\\").\\n  ?extRef brick:endpoint ?endpoint .\\n  FILTER(CONTAINS(LCASE(STR(?endpoint)), \\"alc\\"))\\n  BIND(?endpoint AS ?alcEndpoint)\\n  \\n  # Find the companion endpoint (the one that does NOT contain \\"alc\\")\\n  OPTIONAL {\\n    ?extRef brick:endpoint ?otherEndpoint .\\n    FILTER(!CONTAINS(LCASE(STR(?otherEndpoint)), \\"alc\\"))\\n    BIND(?otherEndpoint AS ?mpcEndpoint)\\n  }\\n}\\n"\n}', part_kind='text')], model_name='hosted_vllm/hosted_vllm/gpt-oss-120b', timestamp=datetime.datetime(2026, 1, 22, 6, 42, 52, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), kind='response')
